sql:
SELECT ka_code, ka_name, ka_description, ka_status
FROM knowledge_areas
WHERE ka_status = 'active';

SELECT project_name
FROM research_activities
WHERE ka_code = 504;

SELECT COUNT(*) AS research_activity_count
FROM research_activities
WHERE start_date LIKE '2022-%';

SELECT COUNT(*) AS active_ka_count
FROM knowledge_areas
WHERE ka_status = 'active';

SELECT activity_name, activity_description
FROM extension_activities
WHERE ka_code = 504;

SELECT COUNT(ea_id) AS total_extension_activities
FROM extension_activities
WHERE ka_code = 504;

external_knowledge:
- Knowledge areas refer to categories of information or subjects in this context;
- Active knowledge areas are those that are currently being used or are relevant;
- Admin permission implies the user has elevated access to all knowledge areas.
